Document: ConvexPolygonShape3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_convexpolygonshape3d.rst  
Summary: Properties of the ConvexPolygonShape3D class, including the points defining the shape.  

PackedVector3Array (Type): points. Default: PackedVector3Array().  
This property stores the vertices of the convex polygon shape in 3D space. The points must form a closed, non-intersecting loop to ensure valid shape generation. The type PackedVector3Array is a compact array of Vector3 objects, optimized for performance in physics calculations. When no points are defined, the default empty array is used. This property is essential for defining the geometry of the shape, which is used in collision detection and physics simulations. The array must contain at least three points to form a valid polygon. If the points are not properly ordered or contain intersections, the shape may not behave correctly in physics interactions.
---CHUNK---
Document: ConvexPolygonShape3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_convexpolygonshape3d.rst  
Summary: The points property defining a convex polygon shape in 3D space.  

PackedVector3Array points = PackedVector3Array()  
Method: set_points(value: PackedVector3Array) → void  
Method: get_points() → PackedVector3Array  

The list of 3D points forming the convex polygon shape. Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedVector3Array for more details.